COMPANY OVERVIEW

174 Power Global, headquartered in Irvine, California, is an affiliate company of Hanwha Group, a FORTUNE Global 500 firm and the seventh largest business enterprises in South Korea. 174 Power Global designs, builds and manages solar power plant solutions. The company brings a decade of global leadership in solar PV to North America, combining best-of-world technology, processes, and partnerships to deliver utility-grade solar PV solutions customized for local energy markets. 174 Power Global offers the full spectrum of PV solutions – from power plant development, design, construction, operations, and maintenance. With proven capabilities across the solar value chain, 174 Power Global minimizes uncertainty and risk, and helps customers achieve a higher return on their investment in solar energy.

174 Power Global through its wholly owned subsidiary, Chariot Energy is a leading retail energy provider in the deregulated ERCOT market. Chariot Energy headquartered in Houston, Texas provides retail electricity to homes and businesses with an unmatched customer experience missing in today’s energy market.

POSITION OVERVIEW

The Business Intelligence Analyst is responsible for researching, analyzing, interpreting, and presenting data related to markets, operations, finance/accounting, economics, customers, and other information related to our business. This position is also responsible for engaging with internal team leaders to align on priorities, define improvement opportunities, and drive the execution of improvement initiatives. Ultimately, the BI Analyst will help ensure we spend the Company’s budget efficiently. This position reports to the Chief Information Officer, or another senior management personnel that the President of the Company may designate.

This position is located in Houston, Texas, and the ideal candidate will be within commutable distance to the Houston office location.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Collaborate with the business to understand broader business challenges;
Work closely with sales, marketing, and operations teams to identify opportunities for new client acquisition and to improve operational processes;
Measure ROI of online and offline campaigns;
Provide analysis of trends and forecasts and recommend actions to improve business operations;
Identify and understand problems through forecasting, gap analysis, quantitative and predictive modeling, research, and statistical analysis;
Collect business intelligence data from sources which may include industry reports, public information, field reports or purchased findings;
Store data in company’s databases, which may require regular updates. Need to establish operational procedures to utilize the database and provide technical support or software maintenance for any unique programs;
Prepare analytical reports to summarize findings and share with the appropriate company stakeholders through established communication processes; and
Perform other duties and special projects, as assigned by Management.

QUALIFICATIONS

A Bachelor’s degree in IT, Finance, Business, or another related field, required;
Extensive knowledge of creating and managing Tableau and/or Power BI reports is required
Extensive knowledge of writing complex MS SQL queries is required
Minimum of 5 to 7 years of relevant business and financial analysis, required;
Effective use of Python for data analysis and ETL is preferred;
Understanding of utilizing and maintaining Git Tools for code versioning is preferred;
Demonstrated ability to develop and apply information-driven approaches to solve critical business questions in a practical manner with tangible results, while demonstrating flexibility to take consultative approach in ambiguous business environment;
Able to analyze large, complex data sets using a variety of software and tools;
Detailed and thorough and the ability to manage projects with multiple stakeholders having conflicting priorities;
Ability to manage time effectively, set priorities and meet deadlines;
Desire to work successfully in a small team environment;
Good interpersonal and presentation skills for interaction with all levels of management;
Proficiency using software programs such as MS Outlook, Word, PowerPoint, and Excel;
Advanced reporting skills using Excel; and
Comfortable working in a fast-moving dynamic, environment.

Chariot Energy provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability or genetics. www.mychariotenergy.com
